4 A BILL
5 TO BE ENTITLED
6 AN ACT
7
8
9 Relating to Shelby County; to authorize the City
10 Council of the City of Alabaster to establish and regulate the
11 operation of entertainment districts as designated by
12 ordinance; and to authorize the city council to provide
13 penalties for violations.
14 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
15 Section 1. This act is adopted pursuant to the
16 authority in subdivision (31) of Section 104 of the
17 Constitution of Alabama of 2022.
18 Section 2. (a) The Alabaster City Council, by
19 ordinance, may provide for the establishment of not more than
20 two entertainment districts in the city, as those districts
21 are defined in the Alabaster City Code. The entertainment
22 districts may contain one or more Alabama Alcoholic Beverage
23 Control Board licensees in an area that does not exceed
24 one-half mile by one-half mile. The ordinance of the city
25 council shall regulate hours of operation of an entertainment
26 district, may provide for the revocation of the entertainment
27 district designation, and may regulate any other aspect of the
28 operation of entertainment districts.
Page 1

operation of entertainment districts.
HB408 INTRODUCED
29 (b) Any retail licensee of the Alabama Alcoholic
30 Beverage Control Board licensed to sell alcoholic beverages
31 for on-premises consumption located in an entertainment
32 district may obtain an entertainment district permit.
33 Notwithstanding any other provision of law, any licensee that
34 receives an entertainment district permit shall comply with
35 all laws and rules governing its license, except that patrons,
36 guests, or members of the licensee may exit the licensed
37 premises with open containers of alcoholic beverages anywhere
38 within the confines of the entertainment district but may not
39 enter the premises of another licensee with open containers or
40 closed containers of alcoholic beverages acquired elsewhere.
41 In addition, the ordinance shall prohibit a person other than
42 a retail licensee from possessing or bringing into the
43 entertainment district an open or closed container of
44 alcoholic beverages acquired outside of the entertainment
45 district during the hours of operation of the entertainment
46 district.
47 (c) The ordinance shall be enforced by the City of
48 Alabaster and shall provide penalties for violations of the
49 ordinance as otherwise authorized by law.
50 Section 3. This act shall become effective on June 1,
51 2026.
